#!/usr/bin/env bash
#
# Requirement:
#   - flock
#
# Author: James Cherti
# URL: https://github.com/jamescherti/bash-stdops
#
# Description:
# ------------
# This script functions as a mutual exclusion wrapper. It prevents concurrent
# executions of the same operation by using a dedicated lockfile.
#
# Usage Example:
#   singleton /var/run/backup.lock /usr/local/bin/backup.sh --verbose
#
# The above command prevents concurrent executions of the
# /usr/local/bin/backup.sh script. Running the command a second time while the
# first instance is active results in an error message and a non-zero exit code,
# which prevents multiple executions:
#   singleton /var/run/backup.lock /usr/local/bin/backup.sh --verbose
#
# Here is the error message caused by the second execution:
#   Error: Another instance of '/usr/local/bin/backup.sh' is running. To be able
#   to run the program again, delete the lock file: '/var/run/backup.lock'.
#
# The second execution outputs the following error message:
#   Error: Another instance of '%s' is running. To be able to run the program
#   again, delete the lock file: '/var/run/backup.lock'.
